I'm just supporting
the boy's fundraiser.

00:39.873 --> 00:41.706
Adult mark:<i> The whole scene</i>
<i> was inspired by</i>

00:41.776 --> 00:44.710
<i>Bob geldof's live aid concert</i>
<i> for famine relief.</i>

00:44.845 --> 00:46.545
<i>While bob held a super concert,</i>

00:46.614 --> 00:49.548
<i> At school we sold</i>
<i> chocolate-covered almonds.</i>

00:49.550 --> 00:50.982
I'll take one.

00:51.018 --> 00:53.351
Adult mark:<i> Being a salesman</i>
<i> came easy to me,</i>

00:53.387 --> 00:57.289
<i> Especially given a certain</i>
<i> someone's sweet tooth.</i>

00:57.358 --> 00:58.524
<i> Pop was hooked.</i>

00:58.526 --> 01:00.826
<i> A junk food junkie.</i>

01:00.895 --> 01:02.360
Aah!

01:02.396 --> 01:04.763
Two more.

01:04.765 --> 01:06.098
Adult mark:<i> I was killing it!</i>

01:06.100 --> 01:07.699
<i> And probably killing pop,</i>
<i> as well.</i>

01:07.835 --> 01:08.867
Mary: Jeez!

01:08.936 --> 01:10.702
Did you make all that
selling almonds?

01:10.704 --> 01:12.504
Mark: Uh-huh.
Mary: Good for you!

01:12.540 --> 01:15.240
Mike sr: Friggin'
packin' ice-box!

01:15.276 --> 01:16.875
Have you got
any more almonds?

01:17.010 --> 01:18.376
I'm all out, pop.

01:18.378 --> 01:19.444
Pop: What?!

01:19.480 --> 01:21.513
Oh, jeez, no more almonds?

01:21.648 --> 01:24.583
Stop your sooking
and eat your breakfast, hm?

01:24.652 --> 01:27.019
Mike sr: Probably don't
need that part anyway.

01:27.154 --> 01:29.354
I sold 'em all
just in time, too!

01:29.490 --> 01:31.256
We have to hand in
our collection sheet

01:31.258 --> 01:32.691
For the 24-hour famine.

01:32.760 --> 01:34.993
Adult mark:<i> I wanted to be</i>
<i> just like bob geldof...</i>

01:35.129 --> 01:36.595
<i> Famous!</i>

01:36.664 --> 01:40.665
<i> If helping others helped me</i>
<i> look good, then, why not?</i>

01:40.734 --> 01:42.400
Mark on tv: Right.

01:42.402 --> 01:44.736
People, I'm here to announce
that I've solved world hunger.

01:44.738 --> 01:46.404
Yes, I said, "hunger?

01:46.474 --> 01:49.007
"ah, not having it."
yes, people want food?

01:49.009 --> 01:50.342
I'll sell 'em
chocolate-covered almonds.

01:50.344 --> 01:52.411
That way I made
800 billion dollars.

01:52.413 --> 01:53.411
You're welcome.

01:53.447 --> 01:55.080
Oh, yes, that's lunch.
Thank you.

01:55.215 --> 01:57.416
Adult mark:<i> And, like bob,</i>
<i> I wanted nothing in return.</i>

01:57.551 --> 01:59.284
<i> Well, almost nothing...</i>

01:59.320 --> 02:02.354
Whoever sells the most
gets a free bike!

02:02.356 --> 02:04.289
And I've already sold more
than last year's winner,

02:04.358 --> 02:06.625
So it's a formality
at this point.

02:06.627 --> 02:08.226
You don't know
how to ride a bike.

02:08.295 --> 02:09.628
Fall off one, maybe.

02:09.630 --> 02:10.729
Well, then, I'll sell it.

02:10.864 --> 02:12.698
I have my eyes set
on the new casio.

02:12.833 --> 02:13.899
Digital!

02:14.034 --> 02:16.568
Melodic alarm,
liquid crystal display.

02:16.637 --> 02:18.704
It shows the month and the day!

02:18.839 --> 02:21.273
This isn't just a watch.

02:21.408 --> 02:23.108
This is a time piece.

02:23.110 --> 02:24.209
Mike sr: Aah!

02:24.211 --> 02:25.777
Packin' packity packer!

02:25.913 --> 02:29.047
[crash]

02:29.183 --> 02:30.649
Mary: Call that repair guy
that works for the station.

02:30.718 --> 02:31.717
Mike jr: I'm already on it.

02:31.719 --> 02:33.451
And that's what you won't!

02:33.453 --> 02:35.554
We don't be wasting
good money on a repair man!

02:35.623 --> 02:38.590
Besides, it's fixed now.

02:38.725 --> 02:42.594
[loud rattling]

02:42.630 --> 02:44.563
[rattling stops]

02:44.565 --> 02:46.398
What's that?

02:46.467 --> 02:48.734
Mike sr: How the...
I was just...

02:48.869 --> 02:51.203
Bloody packin' ice box!

02:51.205 --> 02:54.573
♪

02:58.546 --> 03:00.545
Sister rose: [clears throat]

03:00.548 --> 03:02.280
Mr. Chafe.

03:02.349 --> 03:03.415
Mr. Chafe: [clears throat]

03:03.484 --> 03:05.483
Thank you, sister.

03:05.519 --> 03:07.285
Alright, students,

03:07.321 --> 03:10.455
Welcome to this year's
"slumber for hunger"!

03:10.591 --> 03:12.223
[applause]

03:12.259 --> 03:15.627
I'm sure we're all
gonna have a lot of fun!

03:15.663 --> 03:18.630
Sister rose: Ahem.

03:18.765 --> 03:24.169
While solemnly
reflecting on famine.

03:24.171 --> 03:26.405
If you haven't
done so already,

03:26.540 --> 03:28.507
Turn in your collection sheets.

03:28.509 --> 03:31.909
Later tonight we will
announce the top-seller

03:31.911 --> 03:35.113
And present them with a
gift certificate for a new bike

03:35.182 --> 03:38.717
From "bill's cycle shop,
we also sharpen skates."

03:38.786 --> 03:40.185
[applause]

03:40.320 --> 03:42.921
Adult mark:<i> We put the "act"</i>
<i> in act of kindness!</i>

03:43.056 --> 03:45.457
It's as good as mine.

03:45.459 --> 03:50.329
I-I mean, it's so amazing
we're helping out like this.

03:50.464 --> 03:52.798
Ritche: There were three
bake sales and two flea markets

03:52.800 --> 03:55.200
On my street last week,
so people were tapped out.

03:55.335 --> 03:56.468
How did you do?

03:56.470 --> 03:58.203
My idiot brothers
kept eating my almonds.

03:58.338 --> 03:59.538
I'm way behind.

03:59.673 --> 04:01.340
I hate this crap.

04:01.342 --> 04:03.475
Maybe I could take
a few boxes off your hands?

04:03.477 --> 04:04.609
You know, help you out?

04:04.611 --> 04:07.679
I don't need your pity, dork.

04:07.748 --> 04:09.314
Ms. Fowler: And
before lights out,

04:09.316 --> 04:11.816
There will be games
of bingo with prizes.

04:11.885 --> 04:13.418
[applause]

04:13.420 --> 04:17.289
But there will be
no food for 24 hours.

04:17.424 --> 04:19.791
This is a fast.

04:19.793 --> 04:24.162
When moses fasted, he received
the ten commandments.

04:24.298 --> 04:26.398
What shall you receive?

04:26.533 --> 04:27.899
Fox: A new bike?

04:27.901 --> 04:29.835
The holy spirit!

04:29.837 --> 04:31.636
Mark: You were way off.
Fox: [chuckles]

04:31.672 --> 04:33.505
Sister rose: For when
we feed the hungry,

04:33.574 --> 04:35.841
We feed our lord.

04:35.976 --> 04:39.778
"for I was hungry
and you gave me food!"

04:39.780 --> 04:43.114
Matthew, 25:35.

04:43.150 --> 04:46.250
Imagine if a beggar came
to your door asking for food

04:46.287 --> 04:47.985
And you shooed him away!

04:48.022 --> 04:50.121
Well, what if it turned out
that the beggar was

04:50.190 --> 04:52.924
Jesus in disguise?

04:52.960 --> 04:54.493
How would you feel then?

04:54.495 --> 04:56.528
Adult mark:<i> I somehow</i>
<i> doubted jesus would use</i>

04:56.597 --> 04:57.996
<i> The second coming</i>
<i> to go trick-or-treating</i>

04:58.131 --> 04:59.464
<i> On kenmount road.</i>

04:59.600 --> 05:01.599
So remember, be charitable.

05:01.669 --> 05:04.870
For when someone asks
something of you,

05:04.872 --> 05:09.474
They might just be jesus
in disguise, testing you.

05:09.476 --> 05:10.942
May I use the washroom?

05:11.078 --> 05:12.343
No.

05:12.379 --> 05:16.013
Ms. Fowler, start the clock.

05:16.050 --> 05:18.282
[buzzer sound]

05:18.319 --> 05:20.552
Ooh, nice time piece.

05:20.554 --> 05:22.487
Mr. Chafe: Okay, students.

05:22.489 --> 05:27.359
You can start laying out
your mats in an orderly fashion.

05:27.361 --> 05:29.294
Adult mark:<i> We showed</i>
<i> solidarity</i>

05:29.296 --> 05:31.996
<i> With starving children</i>
<i> by sleeping on gym mats.</i>

05:32.066 --> 05:34.699
<i> One inch of bulk protection</i>
<i> that was almost as soft</i>

05:34.735 --> 05:37.168
<i> As the linoleum floor</i>
<i> it protected us from!</i>

05:37.204 --> 05:38.669
<i> They offered little comfort,</i>

05:38.706 --> 05:43.041
<i> But it was worth it to sleep</i>
<i> mere inches from fox.</i>

05:43.176 --> 05:45.744
What?

05:45.813 --> 05:47.345
So what if it's pink?

05:47.348 --> 05:49.781
It's my younger cousin's.

05:49.850 --> 05:52.650
I don't camp, bum-face.

05:52.686 --> 05:54.552
Maybe I should take the middle.

06:02.262 --> 06:03.862
Give it up.

06:03.864 --> 06:06.964
There's no more of those gd
chocolate almonds in the house.

06:10.237 --> 06:13.671
Oh!
Oh, the floor's soaked!

06:13.741 --> 06:15.473
Oh...

06:15.609 --> 06:16.675
It's dead!

06:16.677 --> 06:19.478
Everything's defrosted.

06:19.613 --> 06:21.813
Oh, no, no, no!
The bulb is gone is all.

06:21.948 --> 06:24.215
Then why am I standing
in a pool of fridge piss?

06:24.251 --> 06:26.718
One of ye crowd must have been
shagging around with it.

06:26.720 --> 06:28.019
We need a new fridge, mike.

06:28.088 --> 06:30.088
A new fridge?
I'll be ruined.

06:30.223 --> 06:31.957
I wonder if it's calling
for weather at all.

06:31.959 --> 06:33.625
We could store the turkeys
and frozen vegetables

06:33.627 --> 06:35.760
Out in a snow bank.
Mary: Mike!

06:35.763 --> 06:38.063
Fine, I'll call freddy
at simpson-sears.

06:38.065 --> 06:39.531
The bugger owes me.

06:39.666 --> 06:40.398
Mm-hm.

06:41.535 --> 06:43.401
Mmm, mmm.

