07:13.834 --> 07:16.601
By a band called
the guess who that says,

07:16.670 --> 07:18.402
"guess what?

07:18.439 --> 07:20.272
"no sugar or other
food groups tonight."

07:20.274 --> 07:22.140
Kids: Aw.

07:22.142 --> 07:24.209
I'd kill for a flaky right now.

07:24.344 --> 07:25.877
And a bag of hickory sticks.

07:25.946 --> 07:30.081
How about you, fox?
Any cravings?

07:30.150 --> 07:31.415
Is she going home?

07:31.452 --> 07:33.885
Her sleeping bag's still here.

07:33.921 --> 07:36.688
Maybe she doesn't
like the music.

07:36.757 --> 07:39.691
Or maybe she doesn't like me.

07:39.760 --> 07:41.926
Mr. Chafe: [pa] mark critch
to the office for a phone call.

07:41.995 --> 07:43.294
Mark critch to the office.

07:43.330 --> 07:45.030
Kids: Ooh...

07:45.165 --> 07:46.765
Adult mark:<i> A phone call,</i>
<i> at school?</i>

07:46.900 --> 07:48.299
<i> An absolute first.</i>

07:48.368 --> 07:50.902
<i> Either someone was dead</i>
<i>or the house had burned down.</i>

07:50.938 --> 07:55.740
That can't be good.

07:55.776 --> 07:58.777
I know you're all
filled up on the holy ghost,

07:58.779 --> 08:01.112
But I hope you left
some room for a little pie...

08:01.114 --> 08:05.583
[applause]

08:05.619 --> 08:07.184
American pie, that is.

08:07.221 --> 08:09.353
Kids: Aww...

08:12.659 --> 08:14.059
Hello?

08:14.061 --> 08:15.393
Is it pop?
Is he okay?

08:15.462 --> 08:16.661
Yes.
It's me.

08:16.796 --> 08:17.862
[sighs]
you're okay!

08:17.898 --> 08:20.131
No, I'm starving!

08:20.133 --> 08:22.166
Who else has almonds?

08:22.236 --> 08:24.368
What?
Uh, I don't know.

08:24.404 --> 08:25.503
Dad bought some?

08:25.539 --> 08:26.738
