08:26.873 --> 08:29.073
Mark: Mom bought three.
Pop: Ah, ate those, too.

08:29.142 --> 08:30.408
Oh...

08:30.410 --> 08:32.343
Uh, dick dunphy
bought 10 bucks' worth.

08:32.412 --> 08:33.411
Why?

08:33.547 --> 08:35.146
Dunphy.

08:35.182 --> 08:37.515
Yes, he'll do nicely.

08:38.886 --> 08:40.418
[dial tone]

08:41.822 --> 08:42.954
[hangs up phone]

08:43.089 --> 08:44.622
Mr. Chafe: [clears throat]

08:44.691 --> 08:46.490
Would you like an almond,
ms. Fowler?

08:46.527 --> 08:49.226
Oh, no, thank you, mr. Chafe.
I'm watching my weight.

08:49.263 --> 08:51.229
Mr. Chafe: I've been
watching your weight too,

08:51.364 --> 08:53.164
And it's looking
pretty good to me.

08:53.200 --> 08:54.665
I mean...

08:54.701 --> 08:56.268
You don't look sick or anything.

08:56.403 --> 08:58.570
Oh, well, you look
very healthy yourself.

08:58.572 --> 09:00.038
Strapping.

09:00.040 --> 09:01.439
That's from all the strappings.

09:01.441 --> 09:02.707
[both laugh]

09:02.743 --> 09:04.742
Adult mark:<i> What the hell</i>
<i> was I seeing?</i>

09:04.778 --> 09:06.844
<i> The only emotions I'd ever</i>
<i> witnessed teachers exhibit</i>

09:06.880 --> 09:09.047
<i> Were anger and regret.</i>

09:09.116 --> 09:12.517
♪

09:12.519 --> 09:14.519
Oh, god.

09:14.588 --> 09:16.721
Freddy says he'll give me
a deal on a floor model,

09:16.723 --> 09:18.189
But he can't deliver it
until next week.

09:18.258 --> 09:19.523
Mary: Well, what
about all this food?

09:19.560 --> 09:21.326
We don't want it to go to waste!

09:21.395 --> 09:23.194
We're gonna
have to cook it all.

09:23.230 --> 09:25.663
Mary: What?
Mike sr: Grab a pot.

09:25.699 --> 09:27.866
Mary: Oh, jeez.

09:28.001 --> 09:30.401
Mark sr: We're gonna have to
eat enough to last all weekend.

09:30.437 --> 09:32.370
Mary: Ah!

09:32.372 --> 09:34.005
Adult mark:<i> My teachers</i>
<i> weren't the only ones</i>

09:34.041 --> 09:35.807
<i> Breaking the rules.</i>

09:35.809 --> 09:38.175
<i> Everywhere I looked, kids were</i>
<i> sucking on contraband candy.</i>

09:38.211 --> 09:41.345
<i>Was I the only one not cheating?</i>

09:41.381 --> 09:44.081
♪

09:44.117 --> 09:47.218
<i> Adult mark: But where</i>
<i> were they getting it?</i>

09:47.354 --> 09:48.419
<i> I couldn't believe it.</i>

09:48.488 --> 09:50.354
<i> Fox was pushing candy</i>
<i> like a dealer!</i>

09:50.390 --> 09:51.823
<i> Like she was me with pop!</i>

09:51.892 --> 09:53.224
<i> What would bob geldof do?</i>

09:53.360 --> 09:54.492
Mark: Get out of here!

09:54.628 --> 09:55.760
Adult mark:<i> Make it</i>
<i> about himself!</i>

09:55.762 --> 09:56.895
What are you doing, dork?

09:57.030 --> 09:58.295
Mark: What am<i> I</i> doing?

09:58.332 --> 10:00.098
Bullies are supposed to
take candy from babies,

10:00.167 --> 10:01.365
Not sell it to 'em!

10:01.401 --> 10:02.567
And at a mark-up?

10:02.702 --> 10:05.903
We are fasting for the needy,
not the greedy!

10:05.939 --> 10:07.571
Fox: Chill out, gandhi.

10:07.608 --> 10:08.973
Besides, it's not eating

10:08.976 --> 10:11.076
If you just suck
the chocolate off of 'em.

10:13.847 --> 10:15.113
Come on.

10:15.115 --> 10:17.482
Everyone's doing it.

10:17.617 --> 10:21.085
♪

10:26.126 --> 10:28.960
♪

10:29.095 --> 10:30.928
No.
No.

10:30.964 --> 10:33.565
Why are you selling food
at a famine fundraiser, fox?

10:33.567 --> 10:35.667
Fox: I told you I was behind.

10:35.736 --> 10:38.269
This is the only way I can
catch up and win that new bike.

10:38.305 --> 10:39.937
You're cheating!

10:39.973 --> 10:41.673
And some of us worked really
hard to have a chance to win.

10:41.808 --> 10:43.408
Don't you judge me.

10:43.410 --> 10:44.843
It's pretty hard not to.

10:44.978 --> 10:46.411
Adult mark:<i> My stomach</i>
<i> was empty,</i>

10:46.480 --> 10:49.947
<i> But like bob geldof,</i>
<i> I was full of myself.</i>

10:50.017 --> 10:52.650
♪

10:54.855 --> 10:58.789
[food sizzling]

11:00.293 --> 11:04.696
Mike sr: Oh, good god,
I feel like perry at the pole.

11:04.765 --> 11:06.297
Rainbow trout?

11:06.299 --> 11:07.832
How long have
they been in there?

11:07.834 --> 11:10.368
Pop caught those in the little
pond up behind the station.

11:10.503 --> 11:13.671
Back before they filled
it in with gravel.

11:13.674 --> 11:15.206
Oh, mike.

11:15.341 --> 11:18.242
Remember when we used to sit
up there and splash our feet?

11:18.278 --> 11:22.246
The flies
were enough to eat ya!

11:22.282 --> 11:24.449
"bursey's frozen cod tongues"?

11:24.584 --> 11:26.183
I remember when
you brought those home!

11:26.219 --> 11:28.319
They were one of your very
first clients at the station.

11:28.321 --> 11:30.888
I was so proud of you!

11:30.890 --> 11:32.057
Let's fry up a feed of tongues.

11:32.192 --> 11:34.459
No, no, no,
I don't like to eat tongues.

11:34.461 --> 11:37.529
I don't like to taste anything
that can taste me back!

11:41.902 --> 11:43.468
The pink poodle?

11:43.470 --> 11:46.137
That place closed years ago.
When were we there?

11:46.272 --> 11:49.273
Aw, that was just before
mark was born.

11:49.309 --> 11:52.076
Bit of spice did the trick.

11:52.145 --> 11:55.613
Yeah, he shot out of you like
evel knievel out of a cannon.

11:55.682 --> 11:58.550
Oh, mike.
Remember when they were small?

11:58.685 --> 12:00.684
Where'd the time go, at all, hm?

12:00.721 --> 12:02.487
Oh, it wasn't that long ago.

12:02.622 --> 12:04.155
It was just...

12:04.191 --> 12:06.357
1974?

12:06.359 --> 12:07.691
Yeah, that might be
pushing it a bit.

12:07.728 --> 12:10.294
